      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/code-verification-level2",
      "rationale": "Each solver has been verified against analytical benchmark problems relevant to structural mechanics (Timoshenko beam bending, Hertz contact). Patch tests confirm element formulation correctness. Verification reports are archived in the project dossier. Required level 2 is met; no higher-order manufactured solution verification was performed, so level 3 is not claimed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/discretization-error-level3",
      "rationale": "A mesh convergence study was performed using three mesh densities (coarse ~85k elements, medium ~210k elements, fine ~490k elements). Richardson extrapolation was applied to stiffness and yield force QoIs. The Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the medium mesh is 3.8% for yield force, which exceeds the project threshold of 2.5% at the pedicle-rod interface contact zone. Consequently, discretization uncertainty is not sufficiently bounded to satisfy required level 3. Achieved level 2 reflects that a formal convergence study was conducted but the GCI criterion was not met for all QoIs. Remediation requires local mesh refinement at the screw-rod interface and re-running the convergence study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/solver-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence was confirmed for all simulation runs; residual norms fell below 1e-6 for force and moment equilibrium. Contact convergence was monitored via penetration tolerance checks. No diverged or non-converged solutions were accepted. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Model setup was independently reviewed by a second analyst at each participating organisation. Boundary condition application, load application point, and material assignment were verified against the ASTM F1717 protocol and the CAD geometry. A formal peer review checklist was completed and archived. Required level 2 is exceeded; achieved level 3 reflects the cross-organisational independent review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-form-level3",
      "rationale": "The chosen model form — implicit quasi-static FEA with nonlinear geometry (large-displacement formulation) and elastic-plastic titanium alloy constitutive law — is physically appropriate for the ASTM F1717 compression-bending regime. Model form selection was justified by comparison to published literature on pedicle screw FEA and confirmed by the satisfactory stiffness predictions at Lab 1. The model form achieves required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-inputs-level3",
      "rationale": "Nominal material properties (Young's modulus 114 GPa, yield strength 880 MPa, titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V ELI) were sourced from ASTM F136 and supplier certificates of conformance. However, specimen-specific material characterisation (e.g., tensile coupon data from the actual screw lot used in the bench tests) was not performed. Inter-lot variability in yield strength (±4%) is documented in the literature but was not propagated as an input uncertainty in the FEA ensemble. This gap directly contributes to the E/uval exceedance observed for yield force at Lab 2. Required level 3 demands specimen-specific or lot-specific material characterisation; only nominal literature values were used, so achieved level is 2. Remediation requires tensile coupon testing of representative screw material or explicit uncertainty propagation of material variability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/test-samples-level2",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories (Lab 1: N=6; Lab 2: N=5). All constructs were assembled from the same production lot and are representative of the clinical design. Sample size exceeds the minimum for statistical comparison at the required level. Achieved level 3 reflects the dual-laboratory replication."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/test-conditions-level3",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) under ambient laboratory conditions (23°C, dry). ASTM F1717 permits a range of test speeds and the clinical loading environment spans a broader range of rates and temperatures (body temperature 37°C, physiological fluid environment). No wet or temperature-controlled testing was conducted. Required level 3 demands that test conditions bracket the COU operating envelope or that sensitivity to condition variation is characterised; neither was achieved. Achieved level 1 reflects that only a single, standard condition was tested without condition sensitivity analysis. This is a documented shortfall identified in the original Nagaraja et al. study and is a primary driver of the Not Accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/equivalency-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions were set to match the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry, loading point, and displacement rate. CAD geometry was derived from the same production drawings used to manufacture the tested constructs. Torque applied to the set screw was matched to the test protocol specification (4 Nm). Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/output-comparison-level3",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs were compared: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Comparison metrics include mean absolute percentage error and the normalised validation metric E/uval per ASME V&V 40 Section 5. Stiffness and force at 40 mm met the <10% and E/uval < 1.96 criteria; yield force did not (E/uval = 2.34 at Lab 2). Required level 3 demands that all primary QoIs meet acceptance criteria; the yield force exceedance prevents achievement of level 3. Achieved level 2 reflects that a rigorous quantitative comparison framework was applied and two of three QoIs passed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the quantities used in regulatory submission to characterise construct mechanical performance. They are clinically relevant surrogates for in vivo construct integrity. Required level 2 is exceeded; achieved level 3 reflects explicit traceability from QoI to regulatory and clinical endpoints documented in the assessment plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/validation-relevance-level3",
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly replicates the ASTM F1717 test protocol, which is the regulatory standard for the COU. The screw design, assembly configuration, and loading mode are identical between validation and intended use context. However, the single test condition (ambient temperature, dry, single loading rate) limits the extent to which the validation activity covers the full COU envelope, which includes in vivo conditions. Required level 3 demands that the validation activity span the range of conditions relevant to the COU; the single-condition limitation (also noted under Test conditions) prevents level 3 from being achieved. Achieved level 2 reflects that the validation activity is directly protocol-matched but not condition-ranged."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-not-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Not accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 compression-bending) concludes Not Accepted based on the following structured findings: (1) Discretization error [required L3, achieved L2]: The mesh convergence study produced a GCI of 3.8% for yield force at the screw-rod interface, exceeding the 2.5% project threshold. Discretization uncertainty is insufficiently bounded for the yield force QoI. (2) Model inputs [required L3, achieved L2]: Material properties were sourced from nominal literature values (ASTM F136) rather than specimen- or lot-specific coupon testing. Inter-lot yield strength variability (±4%) was not propagated as an input uncertainty, directly contributing to the E/uval exceedance (2.34) observed for yield force at Laboratory 2. (3) Test conditions [required L3, achieved L1]: Testing was conducted at a single ambient condition (23°C, dry, 5 mm/min). The COU encompasses in vivo loading at body temperature (37°C) in a physiological fluid environment across a range of loading rates. No condition sensitivity analysis was performed. This is the most significant shortfall and was identified as a limitation in the source study. (4) Output comparison [required L3, achieved L2]: As a direct consequence of shortfalls (1) and (2), the yield force QoI fails the E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion (achieved 2.34 at Lab 2). Two of three primary QoIs pass; the failure of the yield force criterion is sufficient to prevent overall acceptance. (5) Relevance of validation activities to COU [required L3, achieved L2]: The single-condition validation activity does not span the COU operating envelope, consistent with the Test conditions shortfall. Four factors fall below their required credibility levels. Under the ASME V&V 40 framework, the overall credibility is determined by the lowest-achieving factor relative to its required level; the Test conditions factor at achieved L1 against required L3 represents a two-grade shortfall and is determinative. The decision is Not Accepted. Remediation path: (a) refine mesh at screw-rod interface and repeat convergence study to achieve GCI ≤ 2.5%; (b) perform tensile coupon testing on a representative sample from the tested screw lot and propagate material uncertainty; (c) conduct additional F1717 testing at 37°C in phosphate-buffered saline at a minimum of two crosshead speeds to characterise condition sensitivity; (d) re-run FEA ensemble with updated inputs and repeat E/uval assessment across all QoIs and conditions. Upon successful remediation, the package should be resubmitted for credibility reassessment.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
